t/beta_forums/images/smiles/lilkiki.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Lich Rhag`Zhadune </span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/16/02 7:55:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All you non wizards visiting here...</span><hr size=1> The wizard cant blast a mob unless the melees deal a decent ammount of damage to it, otherwise we get munched and crunched. And those mobs also give us a good deal of resists, unless we use the very poor damage/mana ratio lures, which puts us out of the fight faster and with less damage dealt.<br>
<br>
Shamans, Clerics, Necromancers and Enchanters get our 2nd best root (Paralyzing Earth, 56 for Shm and Clr, and 49 for others). And Enchanters also get our best root (Fetter, both of us at 58 ) . I park stuff a lot to help chanters and stuff, but we aint the only ones capable to do so. Paralyzing Earth works very well for it too<br>
<br>
In my XP grouping situations, it doesnt happen all that often that we need to drop something fast. Though I do admit it is useful to be able to do so (provided I can survive it, which gets harder and harder as I level).<br>
<br>
I like the stuns, very useful in the right situation. But ours do damage, so we gotta be careful with mezzes... Plus a LOT of the higher end mobs will get no other effect than having a spell interrupted out of it, if they dont resist at all. Wizard stuns, having 2 effects (stun and damage) get 2 resists, and it's all or nothing, so the resist rate is kinda high.<br>
<br>
As for Evac, its useful, but I dont need it too often either. I can go weeks w/o needing to cast it, and the longer the better.<br>
<br>
And as much as I'd like to have it, I am still w/o my epic at lvl 58. And though I can rune myself to pull, a peridot per pull gets pretty damn expensive pretty damn fast. <p><center>
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132888 "> Kinoel Feuerfaust </a> \\//  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144553"> Ryolas Songdivine </a></b><br>
And then there were two... <br>
