</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/ukinoel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinoel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.sluggy.net/beta_forums/images/smiles/lilkiki.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/16/02 7:55:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord Inquisitor Seru </span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/16/02 8:22:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All you non wizards visiting here...</span><hr size=1> Yes, melees need to work up some agro before you can blast. Nonetheless, with high taunt weapons in the hands of a warrior using all the tricks in the book to keep agro, a wizard will easily surpass the damage of any melees on the super high ac mobs that can be found in luclin. Melees hitting for 1s as often as it happens means if you can just nuke twice per minute, you'll still be outdamaging them. As will other nukers (except mages on mod rod duty), just wizards are better at it than anyone else. <br>
<br>
Yes, other classes get decent roots. Only enchanters get an equal root. Fetter &gt; all other root spells. By far. I'd kill for that spell. Seeing as I often group with no enchanters or bards to do crowd control, having a wizard around to do it is a great thing. If the wizard is good at it, of course, but most seem to be.<br>
<br>
Again, the thing about dropping stuff fast applies mainly to my groups. Like I just said, often I have no real crowd control. And this scenario is not uncommon - Me: &quot;inc froglok dar knight&quot;... rogue: &quot;add&quot;... wizard: &quot;froglok jin shaman dies&quot;... boom, boom, boom, splat, exp... bit later, dar dies. Its nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Stuns are useless for high end mobs, this is true. How much time do you spend fighting high end mobs compared to time spent in an exp dungeon with healing/gating mobs? For me personally, not much. I'd kill for a stun, too. Any stun. In doing damage, wizard stuns are no different from cleric/paladin stuns, and it is something you can work around easily. If a mob is CHing or gating, it isn't mezed. And there's never a need to stun a mezed mob unless you're a paladin about to break the mez.<br>
<br>
Evac isn't as much about whether you need to cast it or not, as the fact that you *can* if needed. Allows you to take far greater risks even if you don't actually end up needing to evac.<br>
<br>
As for epic... well... I was talking about how I view wizards in general, not you in particular, and the pulling part just so happens to apply mainly to epic wizards as that means the puller will hardly ever need heals.<br>
<br>
In short, I don't think the wizard class sucks. Never have, never will. Well ok, one thing does suck about wizards... get the damn familiar out of my face, the flapping sound is driving me crazy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20820">Ulaian Moonleaf</A> - Warder <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144917">Eandil Dayspring</A> - Templar <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.darkwhispers.org">Dark Whispers</A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A> at: 6/16/02 8:43:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/uwizardzapinsommaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wizard Zapin Sommaz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady Vox</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/16/02 9:50:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All you non wizards visiting here...</span><hr size=1> Since very early levels we have known that grouping as a wizard is a constant balance between damage and agro.  During the later levels it should be down to a science such that you get summoned near the end of the fight just before mob dies and you have done a very respectable amount of damage to the mob.<br>
<br>
As for the root situation.. I agree Fetter &gt; all the root spells.  It allows a wizard to contain situations that would wipe out multiple groups by simply controlling a portion of the mobs for the enchanter.  I have often been the only crowd control in many places like Kael arena and found fetter to be very effective when combined with our snare line of spells.<br>
<br>
We do indeed do very fast damage and I have often been the reason that my group gets xp even when greatly over powered by another group.. Sunstrike or Icespear when combined with rain spells drop most mobs fast.<br>
<br>
Stuns I never use anymore.. I know that there are many who rave about stuns but when you get such small damage for such great agro, and with the amount of resists you get I would rather just kill the mob fast rather than bother with the agro of a short stun.  Besides most mobs whose casting you want to interupt cannot be interupted by a stun anyway.<br>
<br>
You have not used Evac in long time?  Perhaps you should be looking places that are a bit more challenging.  Sure on those boring xp camps the group will rarely have need of an evac, but the game is lots more fun when you push the envelope a bit.<br>
<br>
As for the Epic and pulling.. I use it all the time.  The epic can eat the entire HT from most mobs and can save the cleric a great deal of mana.  Even chain pulling the groups I am in are far more likely to slow down for cleric mana than any other caster mana.<br>
<br>
The familiar IS annoying.... One way to annoy your group is to keep it around.  The bug is fixed so /pet get lost<br>
<br>
Sure I am a wizard when you were looking for some non-wizard feedback, but this is not the place to get it.  It is more fun to just amaze a group sometime with what you can do and the feedback comes that way.  It is a good feeling to hear the calls for Evac.. then casually park all the unmezzable mobs out of the way and sit back down while the group picks them off one by one with relative ease.<br>
